<br>
<b><u>Quest #1</u></b>:  Reivaj the Battlerager (he can drop a decent 2HS sword, so I think this <i>may</i> be the start of the quest to get that)<br>
<br>
[Mon Feb 26 01:51:47 2001] You say, 'hail Reivaj the Battlerager'<br>
[Mon Feb 26 01:51:48 2001] Reivaj the Battlerager says 'Greetings, Malkar .  You tread in the halls of Iceshard manor.  Are you here with a purpose or are you lost? <br>
[Mon Feb 26 01:51:54 2001] You say, 'I am here with a purpose'<br>
[Mon Feb 26 01:51:54 2001] Reivaj the Battlerager says 'I do not know what purpose you would serve to the Kromrif.  If you seek to amass a fortune you have come to the wrong man.  I am but a simple battlerager, wielding my blade for the Iceshard brothers when needed. <br>
[Mon Feb 26 01:52:21 2001] You say, 'What is a battlerager?'<br>
[Mon Feb 26 01:52:21 2001] Reivaj the Battlerager says 'Yes, I am a warrior who thrives on battle.  I have great faith in Rallos Zek and I call upon his power to make me more efficient in battle.  I am not like the foolish berserkers.  They howl like animals and create strange totems.  They simply unleash their anger upon the world whereas I focus and destroy my foes with the aid of Rallos Zek. <br>
[Mon Feb 26 01:52:55 2001] You say, 'Who is Rallos Zek?'<br>
[Mon Feb 26 01:52:55 2001] Reivaj the Battlerager says 'The great war god guides my blade and has helped shape my day to day life...  I feel as if there is something greater mapped out for my life than what I have here. <br>
<br>
I can't get him to say anything else =/<br>
<br>
<b><u>Quest #2</u></b>:  Bjoskhua Blackfist<br>
<br>
[Mon Feb 26 01:55:28 2001] You say, 'hail Bjoskhua Blackfist'<br>
[Mon Feb 26 01:55:28 2001] Bjoskhua Blackfist 's lips do not move, though your mind is filled with a voice.  'What is it you want, mortal?  I have little patience for those who do not come here to study.' <br>
[Mon Feb 26 01:55:34 2001] You say, 'I have come here to study'<br>
[Mon Feb 26 01:55:34 2001] Bjoskhua Blackfist looks you over and his voice invades your mind again.  'What is it you wish to study?' <br>
[Mon Feb 26 01:55:39 2001] You say, 'I study knowledge'<br>
[Mon Feb 26 01:55:40 2001] Bjoskhua Blackfist says 'Take this book then, and read it.  Hopefully you can glean some bit of wisdom from it. <br>
<br>
The book he gives you is called "The Story of Porlos".  It's not lore, or no drop... just a book.  Here's what's in it(word-for-word):<br>
<br>
"On the field of battle, many years ago.  A warrior rose above the rest and slaughtered many foes.  His prowess on the field caught the eye of those who we call friends.  In their screams the dragons cried, Hsgara will save us all! Oh they were so foolish, as Porlos was her downfall.  His mighty axe he did raise, and as it fell so did she, the white one who would try to save them all.  Upon her skull did he sit and claim it as his throne.  For the slaying of his mate did the old one named Yelinak choose Porlos as his prey.  Many generations have passed, and the ancestors of Porlos are hunted to this day."<br>
<br>
